# Godot Project Rules

## Engine

- This project uses Godot 4.7.
- Use only APIs available in Godot 4.7.
- Never use Godot 3 APIs or syntax.
- Use `CharacterBody2D`, not `KinematicBody2D`.
- Use `await`, not `yield`.
- Use `@export` and `@onready`, not Godot 3 annotation syntax.

## GDScript safety

- Use statically typed GDScript.
- Add types to member variables, parameters, local variables when useful, and return values.
- Every function must declare its return type, including `-> void`.
- Do not invent methods, properties, signals, input actions, autoloads, or node paths.
- Search the existing project before referencing a node, signal, input action, resource, or autoload.
- Prefer explicit types over Variant.
- Avoid unsafe dynamic method and property access.
- Use `is` checks before casting when a type mismatch would indicate a bug.
- Do not suppress warnings unless the reason is documented.

## Project files

- Do not modify files under `.godot/`.
- Treat `.tscn` and `.tres` files as read-only unless explicitly requested.
- Do not generate UID values manually.
- Prefer modifying GDScript instead of manually rewriting scene files.
- Keep changes minimal and do not perform unrelated refactoring.

## Verification

- Generated code must parse as valid Godot 4.7 GDScript.
- Check LSP diagnostics after every change.
- Fix all syntax errors before completing the task.
- Clearly identify any API usage that could not be verified.

## Glass Wild

- Terminology follows [`docs/core/glossary.md`](docs/core/glossary.md) (`tend` / `walk` / 수역; 벽지 ≠ 배경화면).

## MCP

- Prefer GDScript edits. Use scene MCP tools (`create_scene`, `add_node`, etc.) only when the user explicitly requests scene work.
